Types of VPC Endpoints?

Two types — Interface Endpoint and Gateway Endpoint.

1. Gateway Endpoint:

VPC
 └── Route Table → Gateway Endpoint → S3 / DynamoDB

Detail
--------------------------------------------------------
Services supported : S3 and DynamoDB only
How it works       : Added to route table
Cost               : ✅ Free
Private IP         : ❌ No — uses route table entry

2. Interface Endpoint (AWS PrivateLink):

VPC
 └── Subnet → ENI (private IP) → Interface Endpoint → AWS Service

| Detail               | Description                                              |
|----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| Services supported   | Almost all AWS services (ECR, SSM, CloudWatch, STS etc.) |
| How it works         | Creates ENI in your subnet                               |
| Cost                 | ❌ Paid — $0.01/hr per AZ                                |
| Private IP           | ✅ Yes — gets private IP in your subnet                  |

Comparison:

| Feature            | Gateway Endpoint       | Interface Endpoint     |
|--------------------|------------------------|------------------------|
| Services           | S3, DynamoDB only      | 100+ AWS services      |
| Cost               | Free                   | Paid                   |
| Route table change | ✅ Yes                 | ❌ No                  |
| ENI created        | ❌ No                  | ✅ Yes                 |
| DNS resolution     | ❌ No                  | ✅ Yes                 |

Your EKS context:

EKS nodes in private subnet:
 ├── S3 access        → Gateway Endpoint (free) ✅
 ├── DynamoDB access  → Gateway Endpoint (free) ✅
 ├── ECR pull         → Interface Endpoint (paid) ✅
